# Ex 2

=begin
Use the modulo operator, division, or a combination of both to take a 4 digit number and find the digit in the:
1) thousands place
2) hundreds place
3) tens place
4) ones place
=end

thousandsPlace = 7645 / 1000;

puts thousandsPlace;

hundredPlace = 7645 % 1000 / 100;

puts hundredPlace;

tensPlace = 7645 % 100 / 10;

puts tensPlace;

onesPlace = 7645 % 10;